id: pm-rjh9
title: "GH-190: SDK locateItem should default idPrefix or throw explicit argument errors"
description: Mirror GitHub issue #190. locateItem currently throws low-signal TypeError when idPrefix is omitted from JS callers. Add ergonomic default and/or explicit validation error messaging.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: "area:runtime","area:sdk","external:github","gh:190"
created_at: "2026-06-09T22:33:17.019Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-10T05:14:40.707Z"
author: codex-active-pm-cycle-20260610
parent: pm-5k4v
resolution: Implemented in src/core/store/item-store.ts by defaulting locateItem idPrefix to pm- and verified through the public SDK barrel test.
expected_result: "Package authors can call locateItem(pmRoot, id) for default pm-prefixed trackers without a low-signal TypeError."
actual_result: "locateItem(pmRoot, id) resolves default pm-prefixed items; tests/unit/sdk-index.spec.ts covers the public SDK barrel path."
